==Meaning==
A ''''vial''", or "''phial''", is a glass vessel or bottle, especially a small bottle used for the storing of [[medicine|medicines]].

==Etymology==
The word "''vial''" comes from the [[Greek]] word "''phiale''" meaning "a broad, flat container."

